net.corda.testing.node

Class InMemoryMessagingNetwork.ServicePeerAllocationStrategy

  • net.corda.testing.node.InMemoryMessagingNetwork.ServicePeerAllocationStrategy
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    ServicePeerAllocationStrategy.Random, ServicePeerAllocationStrategy.RoundRobin
    Enclosing class:
    InMemoryMessagingNetwork

    public static class InMemoryMessagingNetwork.ServicePeerAllocationStrategy

    How traffic is allocated in the case where multiple nodes share a single identity, which happens for notaries in a cluster. You don't normally ever need to change this: it is mostly useful for testing notary implementations.
